-- RBS Securities Says Head of Global Currency Strategy Alan Ruskin Resigns
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-07-08T17:22:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/rbs-securities-says-head-of-global-currency-strategy-alan-ruskin-resigns.html

          
          
             Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc,
Britain’s biggest government-owned bank, said  Alan Ruskin 
resigned as global head of foreign-exchange strategy on July 1.  
 David Simmonds,  global head of research, will lead currency
research on an interim basis at the firm’s RBS Securities unit,
the London-based company said an in e-mail obtained by Bloomberg
News. Ruskin worked from Stamford, Connecticut.  Paul Robson  in
London and  Greg Gibbs  in Sydney will continue to provide
strategy recommendation to clients, RBS said.  
 Ruskin joined the firm in January 2006, when it was known
as RBS Greenwich Capital Markets. Prior to that, he was head of
research and managing director of 4Cast.com in the Americas
since 1998. Ruskin was also one of the three founders of
research organization IDEAglobal, according to the press release
from when he joined RBS.  
